## 1. 📋 `AGENTS.md` — The Core Rulebook

> [!IMPORTANT]
> `AGENTS.md` is the **single most important** file in OpenClaw. It defines the agent's operational rules, behavioral guidelines, and global constraints that apply across **all** sessions.

### Purpose
- Acts as the **"Standard Operating Procedure"** for the AI agent
- Defines what the agent is **permitted** and **not permitted** to do
- Sets global constraints and non-negotiable rules
- Instructions in this file are **durable** — they survive context compaction

### Location
```
~/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md
```

### Example Content
```markdown
---
name: my-agent
description: Personal productivity assistant
---

# Agent Instructions

## Core Rules
- Never delete files without explicit confirmation
- Always summarize actions taken after completing a task
- Prefer concise responses unless asked for detail
- Never share API keys or sensitive data in messages

## Communication Style
- Be professional but friendly
- Use bullet points for lists
- Provide code examples when relevant

## Safety
- Never execute destructive commands without confirmation
- Always backup files before modifying them
```

### Key Points
| Aspect | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Format** | YAML frontmatter + Markdown body |
| **Loaded** | Every session, always in system prompt |
| **Survives compaction** | ✅ Yes — instructions persist in long sessions |
| **Editable by user** | ✅ Yes — directly edit the Markdown file |
| **Editable by agent** | ❌ Usually not — treated as immutable rules |

