## 6. 🛠️ `TOOLS.md` — Tool Usage Conventions

### Purpose
- Provides **user-specific conventions and guidance** on how the agent should use its tools
- Customizes tool behavior to match your preferences and environment
- Part of the dynamically assembled system prompt

### Location
```
~/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md
```

### Example Content
```markdown
# Tool Conventions

## Shell Commands
- Always use PowerShell syntax (user is on Windows)
- Prefer `kubectl` over `oc` for Kubernetes commands
- Use `terraform` not `tofu` for IaC

## File Operations
- Always create backups before modifying config files
- Use UTF-8 encoding for all text files

## Git
- Use conventional commit messages
- Always create feature branches, never commit to main directly

## Browser
- Prefer DuckDuckGo for web searches
- Block cookie consent popups
```

