## How These Files Work Together

When OpenClaw starts a session, it dynamically assembles a **system prompt** by combining information from multiple [.md](file:///C:/Users/amitpawar/.gemini/antigravity/brain/5fa8e578-9101-41cb-a39c-d801b6f4c1f4/openclaw_detailed_explanation.md) files:

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    subgraph "System Prompt Assembly"
        direction TB
        A["1️⃣ AGENTS.md\n(Rules & Constraints)"] --> SP["📋 Dynamic\nSystem Prompt"]
        B["2️⃣ SOUL.md\n(Personality)"] --> SP
        C["3️⃣ USER.md\n(User Profile)"] --> SP
        D["4️⃣ IDENTITY.md\n(Agent Role)"] --> SP
        E["5️⃣ TOOLS.md\n(Tool Conventions)"] --> SP
        F["6️⃣ MEMORY.md\n(Long-term Memory)"] --> SP
        G["7️⃣ Daily Logs\n(Recent Context)"] --> SP
        H["8️⃣ Relevant SKILL.md\n(Task-specific Skills)"] --> SP
    end

    SP --> LLM["🤖 LLM\n(GPT / Claude / Gemini)"]
    LLM --> RESP["📤 Response to User"]

    style SP fill:#E74C3C,color:#fff
    style LLM fill:#3498DB,color:#fff
    style RESP fill:#27AE60,color:#fff
```

### Loading Priority & Compaction Behavior

| File | When Loaded | Survives Compaction | Editable By |
|---|---|---|---|
| `AGENTS.md` | Every session | ✅ Yes | User only |
| `SOUL.md` | Every session | ✅ Yes | User only |
| `USER.md` | Every session | ✅ Yes | User + Agent |
| `IDENTITY.md` | Every session | ✅ Yes | User only |
| `TOOLS.md` | Every session | ✅ Yes | User only |
| `MEMORY.md` | Main session only | ✅ Yes | User + Agent |
| `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` | Today + yesterday | ⚠️ Partial | Agent primarily |
| `SKILL.md` | When skill is relevant | ✅ Yes (if active) | User + Community |
| `WORKFLOW.md` | When automation triggers | ✅ Yes | User only |
| `BOOTSTRAP.md` | First run only | N/A | User only |
| `HEARTBEAT.md` | On schedule check | N/A | System |

> [!NOTE]
> **Context Compaction**: When the LLM's context window fills up, OpenClaw automatically summarizes older conversation history and saves critical context to disk. Instructions in `AGENTS.md` and other core files survive this process, but verbal instructions given during chat **may be lost** unless saved to a file.

